The paper discusses the use of distributed dataflow systems for complex analytics tasks, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus of the paper is on the use of asynchronous algorithms for convex programming tasks, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of shared, mutable state, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Database Systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance trade-offs of the proposed approach, which is a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SY).
